Description: Limestone ostracon: on the recto in red ink in three columns a series of name-markers. On the verso several name-markers together with numbers.
Curator's comments: For the type of texts on the recto see O.Turin N. 57008r. Compare for the verso texts also O. Cairo 25315—28, 25651V, O. Deir el-Medina 269, O. Glasgow D. 1925.80, O.Turin N. 57350, 57393 and B. Bruyère, 'Rapport sur les fouilles de Deir el-Médineh 1948-51' (Cairo, 1953), pl. 18.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136381) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136381)
